<TEXT>
the associated press on march 21 reported 
erroneous vote totals in tuesdays special elections in the 14th 
and 18th congressional districts the errors contained in 
tabulations by the news election service did not affect the 
candidates order of finish 
in the 14th district some votes mistakenly were counted twice 
said mike bertha business manager of nes the corrected count gave 
republican susan molinari 28236 votes or 59 percent democrat 
robert j gigante 16593 votes or 35 percent righttolife party 
nominee barbara bollaert 2581 votes or 5 percent and liberal 
carl grillo 437 votes or 1 percent 
in the 18th district nes found minor errors in its count 
bertha said the corrected count gave democrat jose serrano 26728 
votes or 93 percent republican simeon golar 2022 votes or 7 
percent and conservative kevin brawley 118 votes or 0 percent 
</TEXT>
