<TEXT>
police found three children and their mother 
shot to death wednesday in a murdersuicide apparently triggered by 
family and money troubles authorities said 
the bodies were found in a house in the san fernando valley 
about 430 pm by a friend who was checking up on the family 
the children aged 7 to 16 apparently were shot in their sleep 
and their 32yearold mother roxanne fernandez jones had what 
appeared to be a selfinflicted gunshot wound said police 
detective rick swanston 
the family dog was also found dead 
the family had been having some financial and personal 
problems of late and that appears to be the motive said 
swanston 
the children were identified as brandy fernandez 16 leticia 
fernandez 13 and jeremiah jones 7 
the house is about 20 miles northwest of downtown los angeles 
