fires at the homes of two airline company 
executives early today destroyed two cars and damaged part of a 
house and police said they believed opponents of an airport 
expansion project were to blame 
no injuries were reported 
police said they suspected both fires were carried out by 
leftist extremists who oppose the expansion of the narita 
international airport which is 40 miles northeast of tokyo 
in machida on the western outskirts of tokyo a passenger car 
at the home of akio kondo president of all nippon airways burst 
into flames about 430 am an official of the tokyo metropolitan 
police department said 
