officials that he was 17 to avoid return to a california juvenile 
facility from which he had fled 
the states highest criminal court ruled march 14 that district 
judge jack hampton lacked jurisdiction because luan was underage 
prosecutors say they planned to retry luan not just on the case 
that was thrown out but on three other robberies 
in 1986 luan agreed to a plea bargain for three 10year 
sentences only after a jury had sentenced him to 38 years on the 
first robbery 
