<TEXT>
highprofile works of art like those stolen from a 
boston museum are difficult to protect and unlikely to be 
recovered according to some european experts 
interpol the international crime clearing house says only 5 
percent to 10 percent of the stolen artwork it tries to track is 
recovered 
the united states has requested help from the organization on 
the theft sunday at the isabella stewart gardner museum said 
elisabeth gams an interpol inspector 
