alejandro galido in a sworn statement released wednesday by the 
department of justice 
in his statement galido said an american who claimed to be an 
air force colonel and the representative of the us defense 
intelligence agency in the philippines told him in july that his 
agency favors the overthrow of the aquino government and the 
return of the marcoses to the philippines 
the defense intelligence agency is an information gathering 
division of the us department of defense and joint chiefs of 
staff 
galido said the american harold magleo promised to deliver 
shipments of firearms ammunition antitank missiles and 
other weapons for the dec 19 coup attempt provided marcos or 
the loyalist group will give them 20 million for their group to 
produce these war materials 
he also said us ambassador nicholas platt held a party at his 
home in august during which conspirators received written 
instructions from filipino brig gen edgardo abenina who was held 
at a military camp for involvement in a coup attempt in 1987 
in its denial the us embassy statement said there was no col 
magleo on its staff 
galido former military commander in southern luzon said he was 
aware of plans for the coup attempt and he implicated numerous 
military officers and civilians in the plot 
he said abenina suggested assassinating president corazon 
aquino defense secretary fidel ramos and the military chief of 
staff gen renato de villa abenina was arrested in january 
the us embassy states categorically and absolutely that 
press stories suggesting the us governments involvement in the 
december coup attempt are totally without foundation said us 
embassy spokeswoman victoria middleton 
any allegation that ambassador platt was somehow involved in 
contacts with persons plotting against the government is totally 
false and without foundation she said platt was out of the 
country and unavailable for comment 
the united states demonstrated its support for president 
aquino and philippine democracy during the coup attempt that 
support was absolutely firm then and continues to be firm today 
ms middleton said 
she said the party at platts residence aug 16 1989 was a 
normal diplomatic function and among those invited were cabinet 
and military officials including galido 
the latest coup attempt was launched shortly after midnight on 
dec 1 when thousands of mutineers attacked military and media 
facilities seized aircraft at villamor air base and staged air 
strikes on the presidential palace 
us f4 phantom jets from clark air base flew air cover in 
support of government forces and prevented the mutineers from 
continuing their air strikes at least 113 people were killed and 
more than 600 injured before rebels surrendered their last 
stronghold dec 9 
mrs aquinos spokesman adolfo azcuna said the government 
would not comment on galidos statement until a presidential 
commission established to investigate the coup attempt submits its 
final report 
de villa told reporters today the filing of the charges against 
the alleged conspirators will eventually determine whether 
galidos report is credible 
asked why the government and the military if previously warned 
of the coup plot appeared to have been caught off guard when the 
mutineers struck de villa said we did not know the time 
he said the galidos statement of us involvement is an 
allegation that has to be looked into and which the military is 
certainly investigating 
there are many americans here in the philippines de villa 
said there are americans who come and go 
defense undersecretary leonardo quisumbing said other military 
officers gave statements that supported galidos allegations 
i am saying that we have witnesses including officers to 
that effect quisumbing said well in effect that there were 
others involved as it is now coming out in the sworn statement 
they involve some foreigners 
quisumbing noted that galido did not involve the entire us 
government only the defense intelligence agency and a certain 
american officer 
