<TEXT>
when charles stuarts claim that a black 
man killed his wife and wounded him as they sat in their car in 
boston turned out to be an apparent hoax it sounded familiar in 
the atlanta suburb of marietta 
police here too were in the midst of a case of murder pinned 
on a black and nonexistent scapegoat 
neva veitch told police two black men abducted her and her 
husband bobby joe veitch from a motel bar the night of nov 20 
1987 shot her husband to death and attacked her 
police made composite drawings of the alleged killers and 
interviewed more than 20 suspects but authorities made no arrests 
and declared the case inactive 
then in november david lee craig leader of a ku klux klan 
splinter group walked into the police station and said mrs 
