long acts is continuous he loved its impeccable construction and 
he loved those characters particularly big daddy 
i reached beyond myself in the second act to a kind of crude 
eloquence of expression in big daddy that i have managed to give no 
other character of my creation williams says in his memoirs 
watching durning on stage you can perfectly understand that 
statement 
