<TEXT>
the small white madonna is still nestled 
outside the brownshingled duplex where carol dimaiti stuart grew 
up and where her parents and aunt still live but six months after 
her slaying no one answers the door 
the same is true a few miles away on lowe street in revere 
where the parents of charles stuart have maintained a silence about 
the horrifying crime that riveted the nation 
boston police citing an ongoing grand jury investigation have 
remained almost as closemouthed as the families 
the case that took a shocking twist jan 4 when charles stuart 
apparently jumped to his death from the tobin bridge remains a 
mystery 
