an avalanche and flash floods in northern 
india have left at least 17 people dead including 10 border 
guards a government spokesman said thursday 
the border guards on routine patrol in budgaon village in 
kargil district and a civilian were buried under an avalanche late 
wednesday in the remote mountainous area of jammukashmir state 
said the spokesman who cannot be identified under briefing rules 
kargil is 150 miles northeast of jammu the states winter 
capital 
the spokesman also said a bus was swept away by flash floods 
thursday morning at bilol nala near jammu and six passengers 
drowned witnesses said another five also were feared drowned but 
there was no immediate confirmation 
the spokesman said three people survived the bus was going from 
jammu to katuha when a rivulet gorged with four days of rain 
burst its banks 
