<TEXT>
here are the four charges on which the 
joseph hazelwood jury returned verdicts 
seconddegree criminal mischief a felony alleges that the 
defendant created a risk of damage to the property of others in 
an amount exceeding 100000 by widely dangerous means ie the 
spilling of crude oil maximum penalty five years in prison 
andor 50000 fine innocent 
operating a watercraft the exxon valdez while under the 
influence of intoxicating liquor maximum penalty one year andor 
5000 innocent 
reckless endangerment alleges the defendant did recklessly 
engage in conduct that resulted in the exxon valdez being run 
aground on bligh reef and created a substantial risk of serious 
physical injury to another person maximum penalty one year 
andor 5000 innocent 
negligent discharge of oil alleges that on march 24 1989 
hazelwood did unlawfully and negligently discharge cause to be 
discharged or permit the discharge of petroleum into or upon the 
waters of the state of alaska maximum penalty 90 days andor 
1000 guilty 
