does not call for rehiring pilots who went on strike the company 
said thursday 
and the carrier insisted it needs twice that amount in 
concessions by the time the contract expires on july 1 to emerge 
successfully from chapter 11 bankruptcy proceedings 
the wage cut applies to eastern pilots still being paid at the 
prestrike wage rate eastern had 3600 union pilots who honored 
picket lines when a sympathy strike with machinists began in march 
1989 since then many pilots have returned replacements have been 
hired at lower wages and the airline has sold many routes 
time to resolve the dispute regrettably has just about run 
