<TEXT>
the government expanded its recall of 
ltryptophan thursday because of fears that a sometimes fatal blood 
disorder can be caused even by small doses of the dietary 
supplement used for insomnia depression and weight control 
we are confronted with a major public health problem health 
and human services secretary louis sullivan warned in the 
announcement by the food and drug administration 
i urge everyone to stop taking these supplements immediately 
ltryptophan is an amino acid that occurs naturally in some 
foods that are high in protein such as milk beef turkey and 
beans but it is also sold over the counter as a manufactured 
dietary supplement and it may be contained in various diet and 
weight loss products 
it has been linked to a blood disorder called 
eosinophiliamyalgia syndrome or ems 
so far 1411 cases of ems including 19 deaths have been 
reported the fda said cases have been reported in every state 
the recall applies to all ltryptophan products in tablet 
capsule caplet powdered or liquid form as well multiingredient 
nonprotein supplements that contain ltryptophan the fda said 
the only products containing ltryptophan not being recalled are 
some protein supplements infant formulas special dietary foods 
intravenous and oral solutions in which small amounts of 
ltryptophan are needed for nutrition fortification the fda said 
no cases of ems have been linked to any of these uses the agency 
said 
it was not clear whether certain products like diet weight loss 
and bodybuilding supplements containing ltryptophan would have to 
be recalled some of these are formulated according to fda 
regulations the fda said it would issue a clarification further 
defining what is subject to the recall 
ltryptophan is not an fdaapproved drug ingredient and has not 
been considered a drug 
ltryptophan dietary supplements are sold in health food stores 
drug stores and supermarkets retail sales are estimated at 50 
million to 75 million a year 
buyers use the supplement for insomnia appetite control 
depression premenstrual syndrome stress reduction and other 
problems 
the council for responsible nutrition which represents 
manufacturers of nutritional supplements endorsed the fdas 
action its president jb cordaro said i wish theyd done it a 
month ago 
the council has been recommending for more than a month that its 
members stop distribution of all products that contain ltryptophan 
and that consumers stop using it he said 
cordaro said that the largest manufacturers of ltryptophan 
products have taken them off the market and if there are a few 
of the smaller ones that still have it its insignificant 
the council identified the two largest manufacturers of 
ltryptophan dietary supplements as p leiner nutritional products 
corp in torrance calif and pharmavite corp in arleta calif 
kevin lanigan senior vice president at p leiner said that a 
week before the fdas initial nov 17 recall the company stopped 
manufacture and shipping of all its ltryptophan products the 
company also notified all of its customers and advised them to 
remove it from their shelves he said 
neither lanigan or the fda could provide brand names of the 
products since hundreds of products are involved 
kenneth rosenberg chief executive officer of pharmavite corp 
said his company distributed ltryptophan dietary supplements under 
about 20 different brand names including its own brand nature 
made as well as store labels for various retail chains 
pharmavite also stopped shipping its products before the fdas 
initial recall last november and notified its customers and 
provided them with signs warning consumers about the problem said 
rosenberg 
fda spokesman chris lecos said the ltryptophan recall is 
unusual in that normally the fda identifies a specific hazard or 
contaminant and knows who the manufacturer is how much was made 
and where and when it was distributed 
ems is marked by severe muscle and joint pain breathing 
difficulties swelling of the arms and legs skin rash fatigue 
cough and sometimes fever in some cases victims show signs of 
congestive heart failure or develop a condition that causes 
progressive weakness and sometimes leads to paralysis 
sullivan warned ems can cripple it can cause great pain it 
can kill it has had longterm effects on some unfortunate 
individuals and some patients are not responding to treatment 
the fda initially recalled only the larger dose forms of the 
product those that would result in daily intake of 100 milligrams 
or more a day that was based on evidence from the federal centers 
for disease control in atlanta that ems victims had taken 
ltryptophan in doses that ranged from 150 to 17000 milligrams a 
day most were taking 1000 to 2000 milligrams daily 
however at least one case of the disorder has been reported on 
less than 100 milligrams a day the fda said 
the rate of ems has slowed dramatically since the initial nov 
17 recall but officials said some of the recent victims apparently 
had continued using ltryptophan products after the recall began 
the fda earlier was investigating whether ltryptophan itself or 
some contaminant introduced during manufacture or distribution was 
causing the syndrome fda investigators visited plants in japan a 
leading supplier of the raw ltryptophan to us manufacturers 
however investigators have been unable to identify any 
contaminants that could be responsible nor have they linked the 
illness to any single lot brand manufacturer or supplier 
the fdas action was taken after its health hazard evaluation 
board advised that the risk of contracting ems due to the 
consumption of any dietary ltryptophan product far outweighs any 
perceived benefit that may be derived from the continued marketing 
of this product in any dosage form 
</TEXT>
