members as chairman of the appropriations committee returned to 
the senate floor thursday to plead his case 
the coal miners are being asked to pay a very high price 
they will lose their livelihood declared byrd calling the 
assistance program essential to help 5000 miners who are likely to 
lose their jobs 
mitchell meanwhile was working with sen bob dole rkan the 
minority leader to try to get the white house to produce a 
compromise aid package that might be agreeable to byrd 
mitchell and dole have said they are concerned that passage of 
the assistance program would cause the white house to drop support 
