<TEXT>
to prosecutors and the families of his 
victims robert alton harris is a vicious murderer who laughed 
about killing two teenagers and told one to quit crying and die 
like a man 
to his lawyers and closest friend he is the product of a 
violently abusive childhood who during a decade on death row has 
grown into a stable caring remorseful man 
harris has become a symbol of the publics anger over violent 
crime and legal delays in carrying out the states death penalty 
law but april 3 barring a lastminute stay he will become the 
first person executed in california since 1967 
harris 37 was convicted of abducting and killing two 
16yearold san diego boys 12 years ago to get their car for a bank 
robbery that netted 3000 
it seems to me if anybody deserves the death penalty it is 
harris said san diego county superior court judge michael 
wellington who as a state deputy attorney general fought most of 
harris appeals over the past decade 
two murders a pair of kidnappings a bank robbery by someone 
who was six months out on parole from a previous homicide the 
crime is horrible inexcusable wellington said 
michael kroll a writer and death penalty opponent who 
befriended harris agrees the crimes are horrendous 
but he insists the man he has visited weekly for the past eight 
years is not the coldblooded monster drawn by prosecutors and 
should be spared the trip to san quentins gas chamber 
harris has admitted shooting the boys but said he does not know 
why 
on july 5 1978 he and his 18yearold brother danny planned 
to rob a branch of the san diego trust and savings bank but needed 
a getaway car 
harris spotted a green ford in a parking lot john mayeski and 
his friend michael baker sat inside eating hamburgers from a 
nearby fastfood restaurant 
harris pulled out a 9mm luger climbed into the ford and ordered 
john to drive to a deserted spot danny harris who followed in the 
brothers car later testified that harris told the boys he would 
not hurt them and ordered them to walk up a fire trail 
but harris shot john in the back and the head then ran after 
michael who fled and hid behind a rock danny said when harris 
caught up with him the boy screamed prayed and pleaded for his 
life 
quit crying and die like a man harris later boasted of 
telling the teenager a cellmate testified god cant help you 
now boy youre going to die 
harris shot michael four times then shot john again in the head 
at his girlfriends apartment he laughed about the shootings 
and ate the boys unfinished meals danny said 
among the officers who arrested harris a short time later was 
steven baker michaels father baker who learned only later his 
son was dead has waited more than a decade to watch harris 
execution 
they were good boys doing well in school they didnt have 
any problems and on that particular day they were going fishing 
baker said and harris just executed those boys 
in exchange for testifying against his brother danny harris was 
not charged with murder but served 3 years for robbery 
harris was convicted of murder and sentenced to death in early 
1979 but three previous execution dates were dissolved during the 
appeals process 
its just an open sore that never seems to heal baker said 
of the delays 
in january the us supreme court in its fourth consideration 
of the case refused to hear harris appeal on feb 5 a san diego 
judge issued a death warrant setting the april 3 execution date 
on march 16 the state supreme court refused to overturn the 
death sentence or stay the execution harris lawyers said they 
would file another appeal monday in federal court in san diego but 
there are few legal issues left to argue 
last week harris withdrew his request for clemency from gov 
george deukmejian saying he did not think it would get fair 
consideration deukmejian a former state attorney general 
advocates capital punishment and wrote californias current death 
penalty law 
harris attorneys argue his rights were violated and claim his 
progress in prison disproves a prosecution psychiatrists testimony 
depicting him as a sociopath incapable of remorse or 
rehabilitation 
they also have submitted statements from some of the 273 other 
death row inmates praising harris as wellliked decent helpful 
and generous 
unlike most men here weve seen the changes robert harris has 
gone through weve also seen something you wont see on many faces 
here remorse wrote inmate james a melton 
the supreme court petition also offered newly discovered 
evidence of mental disorders stemming from childhood abuse 
harris the fifth of nine children was born in south carolina 
more than two months prematurely when his father kicked his 
alcoholic mother claiming she was carrying another mans child 
he was beaten daily and dropped on his head several times as a 
young child a sister said in court documents that their father 
often threatened them loading his weapons and warning you have 
only 30 minutes to hide 
when harris was 13 after the family had moved to california and 
broken up his mother abandoned him as they picked fruit near 
modesto 
two years later he was arrested in florida for stealing a car 
and spent 4 years in prison then settled in southern californias 
imperial valley and worked as a welder his former wife cheryl 
later testified he beat her and threaten to kill her if she told 
anyone 
at the time of the murders harris had been on parole for six 
months after spending almost 2 years in prison for manslaughter 
his background does not excuse his crimes but helps explain 
them and makes life in prison a more appropriate penalty kroll 
said 
if you treat a child in a way totally devoid of love totally 
violent you will get pathological violence at the other end 
however its manifested he said 
baker and prosecutors argue that harris past was known and 
considered at the proper time by the jury that recommended a 
death sentence 
i believe very strongly that you are responsible for your own 
actions baker said its become so easy and so common for 
people to blame other circumstances 
now baker waits for prosecutors to call him in san diego and 
tell him to buy a plane ticket for the execution 
i think ill feel relieved that the entire ordeal is finally 
over he said 
