<TEXT>
it doesnt pay to mess with a good thing 
take the 1990 buick riviera save for some modifications of the 
instrument panel and more luxurious interior features the car is 
virtually unchanged from its 1989 reincarnation as one of americas 
cherished luxury coupes 
thank heavens in the 1986 model year when buick shrank the 
riv sales plunged from 55546 the previous year to 25835 by the 
1987 model year sales were down to 19838 then to 9241 in 1988 
the signals were clear americans wanted their riv big and 
luxurious 
the 1990 riviera is that and more in fact the riviera ranked 
as the top domestic car and no 2 among imports and domestic cars 
combined in a study by market researchers jd power and associates 
of agoura hills calif the study surveyed buyers of 1989 models 
about initial quality of their vehicles 
for anyone with warm memories of earlier rivieras the 1990 
model doesnt disappoint 
exterior styling retains the traditional riv look with the 
cutoff rear roofline followed by sweptback rear end its longer 
by 11 inches than the previous model 
its solid doors are heavy and close with a decided thud 
the interior of the test car exuded traditional luxury the wide 
front seats cradled the body as did the outer seat areas of the 
back seat leather an 895 option made the test car even more 
luxurious legroom in back was commendable 
three adults could be accommodated in the back seat and even 
the person in the middle had a cushioned resting spot i liked the 
handles that buick installed on the door pillars next to the small 
rear windows they made getting out a lot easier 
oddly the two front seats offered distinctly different 
perspectives on the drivers side the dashboard and instrument 
cluster jut out to put the radio and ventilation controls within 
easy reach and the instruments close for easy viewing 
the instruments by the way were rather jazzy lit up in green 
circles in an arrangement that seemed befitting an airplane 
cockpit this was a simpler design from last years riviera which 
had an electronic control console that some auto writers criticized 
as too complex 
on the passenger side however the dash and glovebox were 
pushed back against the windshield offering a roomy seating area 
that made it easy to cross and uncross legs 
the trunk was wide but had a slightly raised area in the center 
where the spare tire is located the 38liter fuelinjectd v6 
coupled with fourspeed automatic transmission with overdrive was 
nicely responsive and controlled 
suspension and handling were not as mushy as you might expect 
thanks in part to the optional gran touring package 104 that 
added stiffer than normal suspension and goodyear gt4 radial 
tires still the ride should appeal even to those looking for a 
soft ride the test car also had optional antilock brakes 925 
that worked well but kicked up quite a fuss on ice 
as expected in a luxury car the 1990 riviera has a host of 
standard features such as automatic climate control which includes 
air conditioning cruise control amfm stereo cassette and power 
steering and brakes 
i also appreciated the test cars 865 option package that added 
a keyless entry system this niftily lets you lock and unlock the 
doors unlock the trunk and turn on the interior lights from within 
10 feet of the car by pushing buttons on a control switch on the 
key chain it saves having to fumble with keys with an armload of 
groceries for instance the package also includes power seats a 
rearview mirror that automatically adjusts to headlight glare and 
a heated driverside mirror 
buick spokesman gary witzenburg said women account for 56 
percent of the primary riviera drivers and 41 percent of the 
purchase decisionmakers riviera buyers have median income of 
60000 to 65000 and an average age of 50 seventyone percent 
are married and 40 percent have college degrees he added 
with the reredesign of the riviera in autumn 1988 sales 
rebounded to 20000 in the 1989 model year and while buick does 
not make projections for specific models in the 1990 model year it 
does look for overall sales of all buick models to increase 6 
percent witzenburg said 
despite the high quality rating from jd power and associates 
for 1989 rivieras earlier models have not fared as well according 
to consumer reports magazine it ranked the smaller 198687 
riviera v6 models as much worse than average in owner reports of 
trouble 
there were no consumer reports listings for the redesigned 1988 
or 1989 models 
