standard 
the agency has received reports of 146 deaths since 1980 of 
children under age three involving products intended for older 
children but staffers said they could identify only eight which 
might have been prevented by use of a more different test standard 
the potential benefits to change are low said commission 
chairwoman jacqueline jonessmith 
