the rapidly rising land prices that hit the tokyo 
area several years ago have spread to osaka in western japan and 
other regions the national land agency said thursday 
average residential land prices in japan rose 17 percent last 
year with prices in osaka jumping 586 percent an agency report 
said commercial land prices rose an average of 167 percent 
nationwide while business properties in osaka surged 439 percent 
japans most expensive commercial land was valued at 23000 a 
square foot in tokyos marunouchi business district and in the 
nearby ginza shopping district the report said 
prime minister toshiki kaifu owns a condominium in japans most 
