<TEXT>
the blimpie chain of submarine sandwich shops 
said thursday it soon will serve only tuna said to be caught in 
ways that do not seriously threaten dolphins 
blimpies new policy states that no store will purchase any tuna 
unless it is deemed dolphinsafe caught by means posing only 
minimal risk to the marine mammals 
but an environmental group said it advocates a boycott of all 
canned tuna because it knows of no brand available in the united 
states containing only dolphinsafe tuna 
blimpie which says its 350 franchised shops served 4 million 
tuna sandwiches last year will not purchase yellowfin tuna the 
type associated most closely with harm to dolphins 
anthony conza president and cofounder of blimpies said the 
company began working on the tunadolphin issue when it was raised 
by various environmental and animal rights groups 
we believe that the fast food consumer will support our 
decision to take an environmentally responsible stance he said 
blimpie decided against an outright boycott in part because 
consumers enjoy tuna sandwiches 
tuna is a lowfat highprotein food that is highly 
recommended by nutritionists and wellliked by our consumers 
conza said it is not our responsibility to make the decision for 
the consumer on whether or not to boycott tuna 
food distributors have assured blimpie that the policy will be 
followed the company said most of the stores which operate in 16 
states will become part of the program by the summer 
blimpie already serves skip jack tuna from the philippines in 60 
of its southeastern stores and in 28 of its houston locations 
yellowfin tuna one of the most commonly used varieties are 
caught with the involuntary help of dolphins schools of yellowfin 
swim below dolphins so tuna fleets mainly off the coasts of 
southern california and south america search out dolphins to 
locate yellowfin the dolphins often are injured or killed as the 
yellowfin are caught 
dolphins supposedly do not swim with skip jack tuna 
we do applaud the efforts but right now we are focusing on a 
canned tuna boycott said brenda killian a national organizer of 
the save the dolphins project of san franciscobased earth island 
institute we are in support of any restaurants that are looking 
for dolphinsafe tuna and if indeed distributors can guarantee it 
we would like to know 
as far as we know there is no canned tuna being sold in the 
united states that is 100 percent skip jack she added 
the save the dolphins project plans a nationwide dolphin day on 
april 14 to highlight the issue 
most tuna consumed in the united states is caught by methods 
that kill at least 100000 dolphins each year ms killian said 
citing biologists estimates 
