assets of the nations 505 money market mutual 
funds rose 19904 million to an alltime record of 39123 billion 
in the latest week the investment company institute said thursday 
the rise broke the previous record of 39103 billion set a week 
earlier that record originally was reported as 39079 billion but 
was revised upward by the washingtonbased trade group to reflect 
the inclusion of four new funds 
the institute said that in the latest week assets of 247 
general purpose funds fell 9689 million to 13257 billion 
assets of 102 brokerdealer funds increased 6370 million to 
16678 billion and assets of 156 institutional funds rose 5309 
million to 9188 billion 
the sevenday average yield on money market mutual funds rose in 
the week ended tuesday to 767 percent from 765 percent the 
previous week said donoghues money fund report a trade journal 
based in holliston mass 
the 30day average yield rose to 765 percent from 764 percent 
donoghues said 
the average maturity of the portfolios held by money funds was 
44 days up from 43 days donoghues said 
the newsletter bank rate monitor said its survey of 100 leading 
commercial banks savings and loan associations and savings banks 
in the nations 10 largest markets showed the effective annual 
yield available on money market accounts was 625 percent as of 
wednesday unchanged from the previous week 
the north palm beach flabased newsletter said the effective 
annual yield available on special savings accounts called super 
now accounts remained unchanged at 506 percent 
bank rate monitor said the effective annual yield was 788 
percent on sixmonth certificates of deposit unchanged yields 
were 801 percent on 1year cds up from 797 percent 801 percent 
on 2year cds up from 796 percent and 806 percent on 5year 
cds up from 803 percent 
