a house committee approved a compromise 
thursday on tougher smog controls in a clean air bill while a 
proposal for financial aid to coal miners still held up movement on 
similar legislation in the seante 
the 382 vote by the house energy and commerce committee created 
one areas of likely conflict when the senate and house versions of 
the two bills eventually have to be reconciled the senate earlier 
in the week rejected some of the same smog controls 
meanwhile senate leaders worked with the white house and sen 
